HEADWORD: Kilkenny cats
<hw>Kil*ken"ny cats</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Two cats
fabled, in an Irish story, to have fought till nothing was left but
their tails. It is probably a parable of a local contest between
Kilkenny and Irishtown, which impoverished both towns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kill</ent>⟦br⟧
